			<span class="sbi-screenreader">Cinnamon-Sugar Focaccia: For all of your holiday b</span>
						<svg style="color: rgba(255,255,255,1)" class="svg-inline--fa fa-play fa-w-14 sbi_playbtn" aria-label="Play" aria-hidden="true" data-fa-processed="" data-prefix="fa" data-icon="play" role="presentation" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 448 512"><path fill="currentColor" d="M424.4 214.7L72.4 6.6C43.8-10.3 0 6.1 0 47.9V464c0 37.5 40.7 60.1 72.4 41.3l352-208c31.4-18.5 31.5-64.1 0-82.6z"></path></svg>			<img src="https://alexandracooks.com/wp-content/uploads/sb-instagram-feed-images/602934863_1212339577663122_5109348956395596218_nfull.webp" alt="Cinnamon-Sugar Focaccia: For all of your holiday brunch needs and beyond ⁣🎉🎄🎁🍾✨
⁣
Friends, truly, when I first saw sweet versions of focaccia circle my social feeds, all I could think was: why?? Isn’t focaccia perfect as it is?⁣
⁣
Turns out, I was grumpy for no reason. Cinnamon-sugar focaccia is delicious, and it’s much easier to make than cinnamon rolls 🤗 Recipe inspired by @_lacebakes_ 💗
⁣
Comment “recipe” to have it sent to your DMs. ⁣
⁣
https://alexandracooks.com/2025/09/13/cinnamon-sugar-focaccia-no-knead-no-fuss/⁣
⁣
Also, if you’re looking to make this for Christmas morning, here’s a timeline you could follow: ⁣
⁣
Monday: Mix the dough and stash in the fridge.⁣
⁣
Wednesday: Remove the dough and proceed with the recipe through step 8 (after you fold the dough and rotate it 90 degrees), then return it to the fridge in a 2-gallon ziptop bag or covered with plastic wrap. ⁣
⁣
Thursday: Remove the pan from the fridge one hour before you plan on baking it, then proceed with the recipe. ⁣
⁣
#baking #christmas #focaccia #cinnamonsugar #sweet⁣
